article.description: Troymain Crosby had 23 points as Alcorn State defeated Texas Southern 90-75 in a regular season finale on Saturday.
article.headline: Crosby lifts Alcorn St. past Texas Southern 90-75
article.linkText: Crosby lifts Alcorn St. past Texas Southern 90-75
article.story: LORMAN, Miss. -- Troymain Crosby had 23 points as Alcorn State defeated Texas Southern 90-75 in a regular season finale on Saturday. Dominic Brewton had 18 points, 10 rebounds and six assists for Alcorn State (15-14, 11-7 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Corey Tillery added 15 points. Maurice Howard had nine assists. Eden Ewing scored a career-high 24 points and had seven rebounds for the Tigers (15-16, 12-6). Ja'Mare Redus scored a season-high 20 points. The Braves improve to 2-0 against the Tigers for the season. Alcorn State defeated Texas Southern 95-80 on Jan. 6. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
